	faithHeading="Faith and the Bible in Uganda"
	faithBodyHtml={`<p>Uganda is one of the most Christian nations on earth. About <strong>85% of Ugandans are Christian</strong> &mdash; roughly 41 million believers, Catholic, Anglican, and Pentecostal &mdash; with churches that overflow and a faith woven into daily life. The courage of the <strong>Uganda Martyrs</strong> in the 1880s still anchors the nation&rsquo;s devotion.</p><p>The Bible is treasured here. Most Ugandans read the Luganda Bible or English versions, alongside Scripture in Runyankole, Acholi, and other heart languages.</p><p>And yet, amid the scars of war in the north, the AIDS generation&rsquo;s orphans, and deep poverty, many know God more as a distant power than as a near Father. The need is not a first faith. It is to know, in the Bible Uganda already treasures, the Father who draws near to the suffering.</p>`}
